As Ken wrote to Dr. Math
On 08/15/2004 at 16:36:09 (Eastern Time),
>This is what you wrote to me:
>
>A mill is just a tenth of a cent.  So you can convert to cents and
>tenths, and then around that to the nearest cent.  For example, 
>
>  5667 mills = 566.7 cents = 567 cents
>
>   314 mills = 31.4 cents  = 31 cents
>
>So, in other words, what you are saying, if I had to convert:
>
>   $0.034 = 3.4 cents = 3 cents ; am I correct.

Hi Ken,

That's correct.  34 mills is 3 cents, to the nearest cent.

